title: Lucy Sharman-Munday Purchases 4,198 Shares of Eagle Eye Solutions Group PLC (EYE) Stock
content:
Siemens Gamesa Renewable Energy’s (SGRE) Neutral Rating Reaffirmed at Goldman Sachs Group Lucy Sharman-Munday Purchases 4,198 Shares of Eagle Eye Solutions Group PLC (EYE) Stock April 5th, 2019 - Comments Off on Lucy Sharman-Munday Purchases 4,198 Shares of Eagle Eye Solutions Group PLC (EYE) Stock - Filed Under - by Tyrone Williams Tweet
Eagle Eye Solutions Group PLC (LON:EYE) insider Lucy Sharman-Munday purchased 4,198 shares of the stock in a transaction that occurred on Thursday, April 4th. The shares were acquired at an average cost of GBX 144 ($1.88) per share, with a total value of £6,045.12 ($7,899.02).
Lucy Sharman-Munday also recently made the following trade(s): Get Eagle Eye Solutions Group alerts: On Wednesday, March 13th, Lucy Sharman-Munday purchased 10,891 shares of Eagle Eye Solutions Group stock. The shares were acquired at an average cost of GBX 144 ($1.88) per share, with a total value of £15,683.04 ($20,492.67).
Shares of Eagle Eye Solutions Group stock opened at GBX 143.50 ($1.88) on Friday. The company has a debt-to-equity ratio of 52.56, a current ratio of 0.76 and a quick ratio of 0.76. The stock has a market capitalization of $36.55 million and a price-to-earnings ratio of -11.30. Eagle Eye Solutions Group PLC has a 52-week low of GBX 93.80 ($1.23) and a 52-week high of GBX 215 ($2.81). Separately, Shore Capital reissued a “house stock” rating on shares of Eagle Eye Solutions Group in a research report on Thursday, January 3rd.
Eagle Eye Solutions Group Company Profile
Eagle Eye Solutions Group plc is a software as a solution (SaaS) technology company. The Company is engaged in the marketing, validation and redemption of digital promotions in real-time for the grocery, retail and hospitality industries. The Company’s software platform, Eagle Eye AIR, integrates with all existing point of sale (POS) systems and creates digital offers, rewards and vouchers then delivers them to customers by e-mail, text or through a loyalty application for instant redemption.
